	<p><em><strong>stereoroid</strong> replies:</em> That's a little short-sighted; it's the influence of the media that gets idiots with good hair elected. </p> <p>The media influence is nothing new, but it has only been all-important since the Nixon/Kennedy debates of 1960. Kennedy looked better on TV and took the job that year, but Nixon learned his lesson and used it to good effect 8 years later. </p> <p>Can you imagine wanting to be a politician? I can't. To have that desire for power an control makes a politician the wrong person to have any power at all - so we don't vote for them!  8-) </p>
	<small>
	written 8th Apr 2005 <!-- | <a
