	<dd><a name="comment_533" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>Matt</strong> replies:</em> A very good arguement could be made for having some sort of technocratic body running the country. You could have older, experienced people from business, politics etc having some sort of say on how laws are made etc. Older, more experienced people would be more likely to resist rapid, impulsive change, and be less likely to bow to the whim of the media. (Dangerous dogs act anyone? Gun control? Immigration crackdown?)</p> <p>Possibly combining it with an elected government who has to win a majority of the votes in the election, and have elections every few years.</p> <p>Isn't that the system we're supposed to have now?</p>
	<small>
